model_explanation: if Sam only gave Rob bananas, that excludes giving bananas to anyone else, including Tom.
if Sam only gave Tom grapes, that excludes giving Tom any other fruit, including oranges.
if Sam only gave Sue oranges, that means no other items, so giving her apples contradicts that.
knowing that Sam only gave Sue bananas doesn't tell us if he gave Rob anything, so it's independent.
if Sam only gave Tom oranges, then he did not give Tom any other fruit, including bananas.
if Sam only gave Sue apples, that excludes giving her oranges or anything else.
if Sam only gave Sue grapes, that excludes giving her apples or any other fruit.
if Sam only gave Ellen oranges, then giving Ellen bananas contradicts that statement.
if Sam only gave Mary grapes, that excludes giving her apples or any other fruit.
"only gave Bill oranges" only restricts what Bill received and says nothing about what Mary received.
